Measurement section contained a large eddy on the LB which made boat control extremely difficult on this bank.  In order to overcome this difficulty the boat had to remain in the fast water of the main channel.  This likely resulted in an overestimation of LB edge discharge as the eddy was not taken into account.  Loop test was used along with 3 stationary moving bed tests for both measurements taken this day. Sources:Manual

Mmt was collected with WinRiver v. 2.14, but processed with 2.10.   This was a procedural error which may contribute to a small amount of error in reported discharge.  Measurement section contained a large eddy on the LB which made boat control extremely difficult on this bank.  In order to overcome this difficulty the boat had to remain in the fast water of the main channel.  This likely resulted in an overestimation of LB edge discharge as the eddy was not taken into account.   Mag. variation was changed from 16.9 to 17.4 during post processing, however this results in no change in discharge.  Loop test was used along with 3 stationary moving bed tests for both measurements taken this day. Sources:Manual
